"{\"uid\": \"ms.now-opinion-msnbc-opinion-olympics-2024-apology-christians-last-supper-elon-musk-mike-johnson-rcna164008\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Opinion  Morning Joe  RacheL Maddow  Deadline: White House  The weekend  Newsletters  Share this -  Opinion  Conservatives thought they saw a sacrilegious mockery of the Last Supper.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 182, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 47, \"end\": 58, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/White_House\", \"score\": 0.9973899648029313, \"rank\": 0.002616627335415392, \"text\": \"White House\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/White_House\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/White_House\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But that's not what it was about at all.\", \"from\": 183, \"to\": 223, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Themoral panicover a scene of drag queens feasting at theopening ceremony of theParis Olympicsset off afirestormof outrage from religious conservatives and politicians who believed the scene was a mockery of the Last Supper.\", \"from\": 225, \"to\": 449, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Except it wasn't about the Last Supper at all.\", \"from\": 450, \"to\": 496, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The so-calledre-enactmentwas a scene of a bacchanal, a feast to the Greek godDionysus.\", \"from\": 498, \"to\": 584, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After all, the Olympics originated in ancient Greece, and the Greek gods were a part of the culture of that time.\", \"from\": 585, \"to\": 698, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 623, \"end\": 637, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"score\": 0.9999999877873053, \"rank\": 7.213002671745178e-09, \"text\": \"ancient Greece\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 647, \"end\": 657, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"score\": 0.9999999527908596, \"rank\": 4.720916997895451e-08, \"text\": \"Greek gods\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French director Thomas Jolly, who oversaw the opening ceremony show,explainedthat the scene was Dionysus arriving on a table and that it was meant to be representative of the gods of Olympus celebratingthe OlympicGames.\", \"from\": 699, \"to\": 918, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 699, \"end\": 705, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9787331002082028, \"rank\": 0.02074362463696544, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 715, \"end\": 721, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"score\": 0.9994355370924918, \"rank\": 0.0005638162903912545, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\"}, {\"begin\": 795, \"end\": 803, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2951784695549746e-25, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}, {\"begin\": 882, \"end\": 889, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\", \"score\": 0.9999999999822649, \"rank\": 1.762574317284694e-11, \"text\": \"Olympus\", \"types\": [\"Q8502\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tolerance, sadly, is not what conservatives are noted for, especially since many of them deemed the 2024 Olympics 'woke.'\", \"from\": 920, \"to\": 1041, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tell that, though, to those unable to see the scene outside the lens of their conservative religious convictions.\", \"from\": 1043, \"to\": 1156, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They inserted those beliefs into an Olympic celebration put on by the country that had a wholerevolutionagainst the oppression of the monarchy and Christianity.\", \"from\": 1157, \"to\": 1317, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1304, \"end\": 1316, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9905511660239704, \"rank\": 0.009538965994076111, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Criticisms arose from figures such as Roman Catholic Bishop Robert Barron, whotook to Xto condemn the scene.\", \"from\": 1318, \"to\": 1426, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1356, \"end\": 1370, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999999727152, \"rank\": 2.6951078095862026e-11, \"text\": \"Roman Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 1378, \"end\": 1391, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Barron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.038362491248304e-29, \"text\": \"Robert Barron\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Barron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Barron\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French Catholic bishops, who really ought to have known better, complained about the \\\"mocking\\\" of Christianity, and some Greek Orthodox Church representatives condemned the opening of the Olympics\\u00a0as \\\"blasphemous.\\\"\", \"from\": 1427, \"to\": 1641, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1427, \"end\": 1433, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9787331002082028, \"rank\": 0.02074362463696544, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1434, \"end\": 1442, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999995582485165, \"rank\": 4.4172615903442666e-07, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 1525, \"end\": 1537, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9905511660239704, \"rank\": 0.009538965994076111, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 1548, \"end\": 1569, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eastern_Orthodox_Church\", \"score\": 0.9914575412291923, \"rank\": 0.00861512817911366, \"text\": \"Greek Orthodox Church\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eastern_Orthodox_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eastern_Orthodox_Church\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Churches were not the only ones complaining.\", \"from\": 1643, \"to\": 1687, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"House Speaker Mike Johnson, R-La., and Elon Musk, who owns the social media platform X, alsopannedthe depiction of the drag queens.\", \"from\": 1688, \"to\": 1819, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1688, \"end\": 1701, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Speaker_of_the_United_States_House_of_Representatives\", \"score\": 0.9999999997808118, \"rank\": 1.2988480173366952e-10, \"text\": \"House Speaker\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Speaker_of_the_United_States_House_of_Representatives\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Speaker_of_the_United_States_House_of_Representatives\"}, {\"begin\": 1727, \"end\": 1736, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elon Musk\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"C-Spire, a tech company,announced that it was pulling its advertising during the Olympicsbecause of the scene.\", \"from\": 1820, \"to\": 1930, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The organizers of the Olympicsapologized, saying that they did not mean any disrespect for the Christian faith but rather that they wanted to emphasize tolerance.\", \"from\": 1932, \"to\": 2094, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2027, \"end\": 2036, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999967074695267, \"rank\": 3.292541157716335e-06, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tolerance, sadly, is not what conservatives are noted for, especially since many of them deemed the 2024 Olympics \\\"woke.\\\"\", \"from\": 2095, \"to\": 2216, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is fascinating and understandable that the Christians and others who condemned the scene automatically went to the Last Supper as their reference point.\", \"from\": 2218, \"to\": 2373, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2264, \"end\": 2274, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9201117687582347, \"rank\": 0.08677680615460726, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Much of their worldview is limited and does not consider views that fall outside their faith.\", \"from\": 2374, \"to\": 2467, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"First, the classical image of the Last Supper comes fromda Vinci'spainting.\", \"from\": 2468, \"to\": 2543, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It does not represent the reality of what the Last Supper looked like.\", \"from\": 2544, \"to\": 2614, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The confusion and misplaced anger over the scene tell us a lot more about conservative Christians and others than perhaps they want us to know.\", \"from\": 2615, \"to\": 2758, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2689, \"end\": 2712, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_right\", \"score\": 0.9990766119577208, \"rank\": 0.0009242414757841909, \"text\": \"conservative Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_right\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_right\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Moral panics like this one demand immediate strong denunciations and lamentations about the decline of morality and society.\", \"from\": 2760, \"to\": 2884, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Moral panics are designed to take control of any narratives in society that are deemed evil or sinful.\", \"from\": 2885, \"to\": 2987, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In this case,drag queenshave been the cause of a political and religious firestorm not only in America, but also in conservative religious nations worldwide.\", \"from\": 2988, \"to\": 3145, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Second, the fact that Christians immediately identified the scene as being the Last Supper suggests an intellectual simplicity and a knee-jerk reaction.\", \"from\": 3147, \"to\": 3299, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3169, \"end\": 3179, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9201117687582347, \"rank\": 0.08677680615460726, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Had any of these critics looked closely at the tableau, it did not resemble da Vinci's Last Supper at all!\", \"from\": 3300, \"to\": 3406, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The number of people at the table did not even match the 13 who would have been Jesus and his disciples.\", \"from\": 3407, \"to\": 3511, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3487, \"end\": 3492, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999999760893846, \"rank\": 2.391053158411437e-08, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their immediate gut-level response was telling.\", \"from\": 3512, \"to\": 3559, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Not understanding the allusions to Greek mythology or the origins of the Olympic Games and their cultural context suggests that the book-burning, anti-history contingent of religious conservatives has coincided with their ignorance of art, culture, history and society.\", \"from\": 3560, \"to\": 3829, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3595, \"end\": 3610, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"score\": 0.9999981761751121, \"rank\": 1.8238279978808247e-06, \"text\": \"Greek mythology\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's France, folks.\", \"from\": 3831, \"to\": 3850, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3836, \"end\": 3842, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.9839553985383492, \"rank\": 0.01624906053521711, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It dealt with conservative religion and monarchy in its history in decisive and bloody ways.\", \"from\": 3851, \"to\": 3943, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics are being held in Paris!\", \"from\": 3945, \"to\": 3982, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3976, \"end\": 3981, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999969145392, \"rank\": 3.08566240827001e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is a reason there was a whole scene filled withheadlessMarie Antoinettes at the very prison in which she was held, listening to Gojira's heavy metal music.\", \"from\": 3983, \"to\": 4144, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4117, \"end\": 4123, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godzilla\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0530971835760007e-26, \"text\": \"Gojira\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godzilla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godzilla\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's France, folks.\", \"from\": 4146, \"to\": 4165, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4151, \"end\": 4157, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.9839553985383492, \"rank\": 0.01624906053521711, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It dealt with conservative religion and monarchy in its history in decisive and bloody ways.\", \"from\": 4166, \"to\": 4258, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Curiously, religious conservatives did not have much to say about the menage a troisscenethat was also included in the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 4260, \"to\": 4396, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Perhaps that wasn't as sacrilegious to them as drag queens having a bacchanalia.\", \"from\": 4397, \"to\": 4477, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The outrage surrounding this particular scene at the opening ceremony reveals several important things about conservative religion and politics at the present moment.\", \"from\": 4479, \"to\": 4645, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One, trans persons and queer people continue to be the subject of ire and persecution from conservative religions.\", \"from\": 4646, \"to\": 4760, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sexuality is often the first place for persecution in societies that have conservative factions in majority politics.\", \"from\": 4761, \"to\": 4878, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It also signals intolerance for not only these people, but also for the cultural context of the nation France.\", \"from\": 4879, \"to\": 4989, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4982, \"end\": 4988, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.9839553985383492, \"rank\": 0.01624906053521711, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This particular level of criticism against France is not new -\\u00a0rememberfreedom friesfrom the Iraqi War?\", \"from\": 4991, \"to\": 5094, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5034, \"end\": 5040, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.9839553985383492, \"rank\": 0.01624906053521711, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That did not last long, and I suspect this new moral panic will not last over the course of the Olympics.\", \"from\": 5095, \"to\": 5200, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After all, the outrage only shows just how limited in scope their imaginations are.\", \"from\": 5202, \"to\": 5285, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Anthea Butler    Anthea Butler is a professor of religious studies and Africana studies at the University of Pennsylvania.\", \"from\": 5287, \"to\": 5409, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5287, \"end\": 5300, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anthea_Butler\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anthea Butler\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anthea_Butler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anthea_Butler\"}, {\"begin\": 5304, \"end\": 5317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anthea_Butler\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anthea Butler\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anthea_Butler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anthea_Butler\"}, {\"begin\": 5358, \"end\": 5374, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Black_studies\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Africana studies\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Black_studies\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Black_studies\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a9\\u00a02025 Versant Media, LLC\", \"from\": 5411, \"to\": 5436, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5418, \"end\": 5425, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Versant\", \"score\": 0.9999992426422207, \"rank\": 7.573584593083167e-07, \"text\": \"Versant\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Versant\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Versant\"}, {\"begin\": 5433, \"end\": 5436, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_liability_company\", \"score\": 0.999439621660692, \"rank\": 0.0005606925392654915, \"text\": \"LLC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_liability_company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_liability_company\"}]}]}"